First Lady Melania Trump and First Lady Maria Juliana Ruiz Sandoval of Colombia discussed the opioid crisis in the United States during a lunch at the White House. They talked about the devastating impact of the crisis, especially on children and young mothers. Melania Trump also addressed the issue of drug addiction among youth and discussed her initiative, Be Best, which aims to raise awareness about substance abuse. She emphasized the importance of continuing to raise awareness about the harm caused by opioids and expressed her commitment to fighting the addiction crisis globally.